  "profile": {
    "id": "griffiths_squibb_fig6",
    "title": {
      "en": "Prof. Griffiths (G3ZIL) et al. RX Comparison: Day/Night SNR Reversal: Low Dipole vs Vertical"
    },
    "description": {
      "en": "[Publication: Griffiths, G., & Squibb, N. J. (2017). Improving HF band SNR from analysis of WSPR spots](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/319903566_Improving_HF_Band_SNR_from_analysis_of_WSPR_spots)  \n\n Re-examines Griffiths & Squibb Fig. 6 for 5–7 April 2017 by folding same-cycle paired ΔSNR by UTC hour. In RX Compare → Segment Insight, G4HZX’s vertical leads around 01–04 UTC (median down to about −3 dB); after about 05 UTC, G3ZIL’s low dipole leads by typically +5 to +8 dB through most of the day."
    }
  },
